  "prompt": "Which are the top startups in India?",
  "response": "As of my last knowledge update in October 2023, several Indian startups have gained significant attention and traction, making them some of the top players in the ecosystem. Here are some notable ones across various sectors:\n\n1. **BYJU'S** - An edtech company that offers online tutoring and learning materials for students. It has become one of the largest edtech companies in the world.\n\n2. **Ola** - A ride-hailing platform that competes with Uber in India and has expanded into electric mobility and international markets.\n\n3. **Zomato** - A food delivery and restaurant aggregator service that went public and has expanded into grocery delivery and more international markets.\n\n4. **Paytm** - A digital payments and financial services company that offers a wide range of services, including mobile recharges, utility payments, and financial products.\n\n5. **Swiggy** - Another major player in food delivery, Swiggy has expanded its services to include grocery delivery and instant commerce through Swiggy Genie.\n\n6. **CRED** - A fintech platform that rewards users for paying their credit card bills on time and offers various financial products.\n\n7. **Razorpay** - A payments gateway that provides businesses with payment solutions, such as payment processing and invoicing.\n\n8. **Meesho** - A social commerce platform that enables small businesses and individuals to start their online stores through social media.\n\n9. **Udaan** - A B2B e-commerce platform that connects manufacturers and suppliers with retailers across various industries.\n\n10. **Urban Company** (formerly UrbanClap) - A home services marketplace that connects customers with service professionals for various services, including beauty, cleaning, and repairs.\n\n11. **Bounce** - A scooter rental service that has expanded into electric mobility solutions.\n\n12. **CredAvenue** - A platform that connects borrowers and lenders, focusing on providing debt solutions to businesses.\n\nKeep in mind that the landscape of startups is dynamic, with new companies emerging and existing ones evolving rapidly. Therefore, it's advisable to check the latest news and rankings for the most up-to-date information on India's top startups.",
